<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="587" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,150,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,186,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Distribution.</emphasis>
Previously known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[706,802,186,212]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="World Spider Catalog" box="[821,1145,186,212]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" refId="ref4101" refString="World Spider Catalog (2022) World Spider Catalog. Version 23.0. Natural History Museum Bern, Bern. Available from: http: // wsc. nmbe. ch (accessed 22 January 2022) https: // doi. org / 10.24436 / 2" type="book" year="2022">World Spider Catalog 2022</bibRefCitation>
), and here reported from North 
<collectingCountry box="[224,348,222,248]" name="Macedonia" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Macedonia</collectingCountry>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
